00:00:05.040 --> 00:00:10.080
I am George William Gordon born in&nbsp;
1820 in Mavis Bank, Jamaica. I was a&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:10.080 --> 00:00:14.400
Jamaican businessman and politician who was a&nbsp;
critic of the British policies in my country.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:14.960 --> 00:00:19.040
I was executed due to my opinions which&nbsp;
created a huge controversy in Britain,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:19.040 --> 00:00:24.400
and I was proclaimed a National Hero of Jamaica.
 
My father is a Scottish Planter and attorney to&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:24.400 --> 00:00:28.960
several sugar estates in Jamaica. I went to&nbsp;
live with my godfather in Black River and&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:28.960 --> 00:00:34.240
completed my education there. Within a year,&nbsp;
I began working in my grandfatherâ€™s business.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:34.240 --> 00:00:37.680
I became a large landowner,&nbsp;
shopkeeper, produce dealer,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:37.680 --> 00:00:42.640
preacher, social worker, and philanthropist.
 
In the face of attempts to crush the spirit of&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:42.640 --> 00:00:47.200
the freed people of Jamaica and again reduce&nbsp;
them to slavery, I entered politics and faced&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:47.200 --> 00:00:51.440
severe odds, as the people whose interests&nbsp;
I sought to serve did not qualify to vote.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:56.720
I subdivided my own lands, selling farm&nbsp;
lots to the people as cheaply as possible,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:56.720 --> 00:01:00.800
and organized a marketing system, through which&nbsp;
they could sell their produce at fair prices.
