00:01:01.440 --> 00:01:06.720
My public life began about 1844 when I entered&nbsp;
politics as an advocate for the poverty-stricken&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:06.720 --> 00:01:12.720
African-enslaved peasants. In 1865, the&nbsp;
economic condition in Jamaica had gotten worse.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:13.360 --> 00:01:17.600
I spoke openly on behalf of the poor Africans&nbsp;
and with bitter criticism of the government.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:18.240 --> 00:01:22.240
During this period of oppression,&nbsp;
the Morant Bay rebellion broke out.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:22.240 --> 00:01:26.480
It was led by Paul Bogle, an activist in&nbsp;
revolting against the system of government.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:27.040 --> 00:01:30.400
They raided a police station for arms&nbsp;
and the Court House in Morant Bay.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:31.040 --> 00:01:35.680
It was from this incident that a warrant was&nbsp;
done for my arrest. As soon as I knew it,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:35.680 --> 00:01:41.520
I turned myself in to authorities. Despite&nbsp;
lack of evidence, I was executed in 1865.

00:01:42.080 --> 00:01:46.320
In the aftermath of the labor rebellion, I&nbsp;
came to be seen as a precursor of Jamaican&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:46.320 --> 00:01:51.440
nationalism and was given the nation's highest&nbsp;
honor, Order of National Hero. I lived giving&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:51.440 --> 00:01:55.440
whatever I had for the less fortunate wishing&nbsp;
for a ripple effect that will spread all over&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:55.440 --> 00:01:56.489
the world. 

